This paper deals with the statistical properties of Voronoi tessellations, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also discusses the application of these properties to wireless sensor networks, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mathematical methods to calculate the distribution of cell area, which could be considered as a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
